🔥 ASSIGNMENT 8 — FIREBASE AUTHENTICATION + FIRESTORE DATABASE
COMPLETE FINAL STEP-BY-STEP PRACTICAL SHEET
This is the clean final execution flow for Firebase Authentication and Firestore Database practical.

🎯 AIM
To create a Firebase project, enable Google Authentication, and store user data in Firestore Database.

🧠 REQUIREMENTS
✅ Google Account ✅ Internet Connection ✅ Browser

🌐 COMPLETE FLOW
Open Firebase
↓
Create Firebase Project
↓
Enable Authentication
↓
Enable Google Sign-In
↓
Create Firestore Database
↓
Create Collection
↓
Insert Document
↓
Verify Data Storage

✅ STEP 1 — OPEN FIREBASE CONSOLE
Open:
Firebase Console
Login using Google account.

✅ STEP 2 — CREATE FIREBASE PROJECT
Click:
Create a Project

ENTER PROJECT NAME
Example:
CloudPractical

CLICK:
Continue

OPTIONAL
Google Analytics: ✅ Keep OFF for practical.

CLICK:
Create Project

🎉 FIREBASE PROJECT CREATED

✅ STEP 3 — OPEN AUTHENTICATION SERVICE
In left sidebar open:
Build → Authentication

CLICK:
Get Started

🎯 WHAT IS AUTHENTICATION?
Authentication is used to: ✅ verify user identity/login.

✅ STEP 4 — ENABLE GOOGLE SIGN-IN
Open:
Sign-in Method

SELECT:
Google

CLICK:
Enable

SELECT SUPPORT EMAIL
Choose your Gmail account.

CLICK:
Save

🎉 GOOGLE AUTHENTICATION ENABLED
Now users can: ✅ login using Google account.

✅ STEP 5 — OPEN FIRESTORE DATABASE
In left sidebar open:
Build → Firestore Database

CLICK:
Create Database

🎯 WHAT IS FIRESTORE?
Firestore is: ✅ NoSQL cloud database.
Used to: ✅ store application data online.

✅ STEP 6 — SELECT DATABASE MODE
Choose:
Start in test mode

🎯 WHY TEST MODE?
Allows: ✅ easy read/write operations during practical.

CLICK:
Next

✅ STEP 7 — SELECT REGION
Choose nearby region.
Example:
asia-south1

CLICK:
Enable

🎉 FIRESTORE DATABASE CREATED

✅ STEP 8 — CREATE COLLECTION
Click:
Start Collection

ENTER COLLECTION NAME
Example:
Users

CLICK:
Next

🎯 WHAT IS COLLECTION?
Collection = group of related documents.
Similar to:
table
in SQL databases.

✅ STEP 9 — CREATE DOCUMENT
For:
Document ID
Choose:
Auto-ID

✅ ADD DOCUMENT FIELDS
Field	Type	Value
name	string	Sonam
email	string	sonam@gmail.com
CLICK:
Save

🎉 DOCUMENT STORED SUCCESSFULLY

✅ STEP 10 — VERIFY DATA
Now you’ll see:
Users
collection containing: ✅ stored document data.

🎯 WHAT HAPPENED INTERNALLY?
User data entered
↓
Stored inside Firestore
↓
Managed by Firebase cloud

🎉 PRACTICAL COMPLETED
You successfully: ✅ created Firebase project ✅ enabled Google Authentication ✅ created Firestore database ✅ created collection ✅ inserted document data

